e 162.84 area all the way to a low of 160.60 \u2014 a move that tested the prior reaction zone around 160.60, a level that has now registered four distinct touches and held on each occasion. That zone has clearly been a meaningful area for participants, and the subsequent recovery has been orderly rather than impulsive, which tends to suggest the dip was absorbed rather than ignored. From the 6th of July onwards, the daily structure has produced a sequence of higher lows and the pair has reclaimed the 162.00 handle with conviction. The broader cluster of support zones between 159.42 and 160.60 remains well beneath current price, providing a layered floor should any deeper retracement materialise.\n\nOn the H1 timeframe, the past 24 hours have been notably range-bound. Price spiked to a session high of 162.74 during the early Asian session on the 20th before retreating sharply, and since then the hourly bars have been consolidating in a narrow corridor roughly between 162.31 and 162.54. The 162.30\u2013162.35 area is acting as an intraday structure floor, while the 162.50\u2013162.55 region has capped several recovery attempts through the European morning. The consolidation pattern following a spike high is worth monitoring \u2014 it can resolve either as a continuation or as a distribution phase depending on how price interacts with those boundaries into the afternoon.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes the prospect of scheduled macro volatility. With no data releases or central bank speakers flagged, price action is likely to remain technically driven, and the compressed ranges seen across recent sessions may persist. That said, thin calendar conditions can occasionally produce exaggerated moves on relatively modest order flow, particularly heading into the weekly close.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure on a daily close back below 161.70, the area that has acted as a pivot on several recent sessions. A sustained move beneath 161.30 would begin to challenge the recovery narrative more meaningfully, and a return to the 160.60 prior reaction zone would represent a significant structural deterioration. For now, the weight of evidence on the daily chart continues to favour the upside scenario, with the 162.84 recent high the natural reference point for any extension of the current advance.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}